Task 1: Understanding Cyber Security Basics & Attack Surface:

1.What is means Cyber Security?
    *Cyber Security is Domain of Protecting our Digital Assets such as Data, System, Network, Applicaions and Network Connected Devices using Cyber Security related technologies,
     Process and Methodologies.
    *By Preventing the Cyber Attacks, unauthorized Access, Data theft , Data breaches and all the Other Cyber and Digital related Criminal Activities and Forgeries.
    *In Cyber Security People Ensures that our Data, System and Applications are in Safe and Protected using the CIA Traid,
      *(C--> Confidentiality)
      *(I--> Integrity)
      *(A--> Availability)

 i) C--> Confidentiality:
      *Confidentiality means in an organization the Data, Systems, Networks and Applications are Protected from Unauthorized peoples and Other Criminal Related Activities
      *By Using Encription/Decryptions Methods in the Communication Medium to the Sender/Receiver
      *This Ensure that our Digital Assets are in safely
      *This is Knowns as Confidentiality

ii) I--> Integrity:
      * Integrity means our data is 100% accurate, Completeness and Trustworthiness during the Communication and the Other Mediums without any malicious tampering, Alternatives, Modifications.
      * By using Version Control for tampering, File Permissions for the Alternatives and modifications, Checking Digital Signatures and using Checksums.
      * This will Ensures the Integrity ensures the Sender/Receiver that is our data is safe.

iii) A--> Availability:
      * Availability means Our data is Accesed by Authorized users when needed.
      * It Ensures that our data can be Access by Authorized users only not Others like Unauthorized users
      * Availability ensures in anywhere, Anytime we can access the data like disaster time and other Problamatic times 
      * If our data servers are facing slowdown, crashes, cyber attacks and other problems , Our data is being Beckuped and Stored for other backup or recovery servers for Data Recovery.
      * This Ensures that Our Data is Safe.

